docs\progress\logs\20260625-040736_execute-P002.log:3025:I realize that later, the `completeTask` function marks the plan file and ensures the status is updated as completed without updating the duration. It only updates the `updated_at` field. Meanwhile, the current `completeTask` updates the database too. So, it can use `UPDATE plan_tasks SET status='completed', updated_at=?` to avoid accumulating changes. If `completeTask` runs after `executeTask` is successful, the status is already completed, so it shouldn't cause any issues.
